          'Protection relay coordination: in large UPS installations, protection relays (overcurrent, ground fault, differential) coordinate with UPS output breakers to isolate faults without unnecessarily tripping the UPS. Improper coordination or failed relays are common sources of unexpected UPS trips that should be investigated and corrected.',
